docs.lead_paragraph: At first glance, Colorado seems to be one of the federal law’s clearest success stories. But zoom in closer, and it is clear that a kind of pricing pandemonium is underway.

headline.main: In Colorado, Disparity in Health Plan Prices Underscores Ambitions, and Limits, of Affordable Care Act

docs.abstract: Colorado's health insurance exchange has big disparity in premium prices, highlighting volatility of health plans under Affordable Care Act; some insurers are experimenting with very low prices that might not be sustainable over several years, while residents in state's resort areas pay relatively high premiums.
docs.snippet: At first glance, Colorado seems to be one of the federal law’s clearest success stories. But zoom in closer, and it is clear that a kind of pricing pandemonium is underway.

docs.lead_paragraph: Why do so many Americans hold views that are completely at odds with, and completely unaffected by, actual experience?
docs.abstract: Paul Krugman Op-Ed column asserts that conservative dogma has come to dominate several important United States policy discussions--including climate change, health care and the economy--with entrenched opinion trumping evidence; holds that position that unites disparate issues is rejection of government's role in helping ordinary citizens; suggests that underlying motivation is fear of any hierarchical disruption that elevates common person.
